1) To create a class in Python, use the keyworld 'class'  followed by the desired class name in CamelCase.

class Dataset:
  def __init__(self):
    self.type ='csv'
    
#use __init__() method defined to instantiate the object.
#self variable refers to the created object so you can interact with the instance data



2) To create a dataset object

new_dataset = Dataset()

#new_dataset variable refers tp an instance pf the Dataset class



3) To add data to dataset object on instantiation, have to add an additional argument to the __init__() method. (Note: Keep self variable)

class Dataset:
  def __init__(self, data):
    self.type = 'csv
    self.data = data

f= open('nfl.csv','r')
csvreader = csv.reader(f)
nfl_data = list(csvreader)
#read data from csv

nfl_dataset = Dataset(nfl_data)
#create an instance class pass in nfl_data to the __init__() method.
# print (nfl_dataset) returns to the object id

dataset_data = nfl_dataset.data
#print (dataset_data) returns to the data from csv
